---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — HNB Investment Bank"
  description="How HNB Investment Bank collects, uses, and protects your personal information."
>

<div class="page-header"><div class="page-header-inner">
  <div class="page-header-eyebrow">Legal</div>
  <h1 class="page-header-h1">Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="page-header-lead">How HNB Investment Bank collects, uses, and protects your personal information.</p>
</div></div>

<section class="section-pad">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="legal-body">
      <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: 01 January 2024 &nbsp;|&nbsp; Effective: 01 January 2024</p>

      <div class="legal-toc">
        <h4>Contents</h4>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#s1">Who We Are</a></li>
          <li><a href="#s2">Information We Collect</a></li>
          <li><a href="#s3">How We Use Your Information</a></li>
          <li><a href="#s4">Legal Basis for Processing</a></li>
          <li><a href="#s5">Sharing of Information</a></li>
          <li><a href="#s6">Data Retention</a></li>
          <li><a href="#s7">Your Rights</a></li>
          <li><a href="#s8">Security</a></li>
          <li><a href="#s9">Cookies</a></li>
          <li><a href="#s10">Changes to This Policy</a></li>
          <li><a href="#s11">Contact Us</a></li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <h2 id="s1">1. Who We Are</h2>
      <p>HNB Investment Bank Limited ("we", "us", "our") is a licensed investment bank incorporated in Sri Lanka. Our registered office is at No. 53 Dharmapala Mawatha, Colombo 03, Sri Lanka. We are regulated by the Securities and Exchange Commission of Sri Lanka (SEC) and the Central Bank of Sri Lanka (CBSL).</p>
      <p>This Privacy Policy applies to all services offered by HNB Investment Bank and its subsidiaries, including HNB Stockbrokers (Pvt) Ltd, HNB Securities Ltd, and Lanka Ventures Limited.</p>

      <h2 id="s2">2. Information We Collect</h2>
      <h3>2.1 Information You Provide</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Identity information: full name, NIC/passport number, date of birth, gender</li>
        <li>Contact information: postal address, email address, telephone numbers</li>
        <li>Financial information: bank account details, investment history, risk profile, net worth declarations</li>
        <li>Business information: company name, registration number, directors, UBO details (for corporate clients)</li>
        <li>Documentation: KYC documents, source of funds declarations, signed agreements</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>2.2 Information We Collect Automatically</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Website usage data: IP address, browser type, pages visited, session duration</li>
        <li>Device information: device type, operating system, unique device identifiers</li>
        <li>Transaction data: trade orders, settlement records, portfolio valuations</li>
        <li>Communication records: call recordings (where legally required), email correspondence</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>2.3 Information from Third Parties</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Credit reference agencies and financial crime screening databases</li>
        <li>Colombo Stock Exchange (CSE) and Central Depository Systems (CDS)</li>
        <li>Regulatory bodies (SEC, CBSL, FIU-SL) where lawfully required</li>
        <li>Publicly available sources such as company registries and official gazettes</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="s3">3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To open and manage your investment account(s)</li>
        <li>To execute securities transactions on your behalf</li>
        <li>To comply with Anti-Money Laundering (AML) and Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations</li>
        <li>To provide investment research, market information, and advisory services</li>
        <li>To detect, prevent, and investigate fraud and financial crime</li>
        <li>To respond to your enquiries and provide customer support</li>
        <li>To send account statements, trade confirmations, and regulatory notices</li>
        <li>To improve our website and digital services through analytics</li>
        <li>To comply with tax reporting obligations (including FATCA and CRS)</li>
        <li>To send marketing communications where you have given consent</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="s4">4. Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
      <p>We process your personal data on the following legal bases:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Contract performance:</strong> processing necessary to open your account and provide our services</li>
        <li><strong>Legal obligation:</strong> compliance with SEC regulations, CBSL directives, FIU-SL requirements, and tax laws</li>
        <li><strong>Legitimate interests:</strong> fraud prevention, IT security, improving our services, and direct marketing to existing clients</li>
        <li><strong>Consent:</strong> marketing communications to prospective clients; you may withdraw consent at any time</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="s5">5. Sharing of Information</h2>
      <p>We do not sell your personal data. We may share your information with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Our subsidiaries and affiliated entities within the HNB Group</li>
        <li>The Colombo Stock Exchange (CSE) and CDS as required for securities settlement</li>
        <li>Regulatory authorities (SEC, CBSL, FIU-SL, IRD) when legally compelled</li>
        <li>Third-party service providers (custodians, IT providers, auditors) under strict confidentiality agreements</li>
        <li>Legal and compliance advisors for the purposes of obtaining legal advice</li>
        <li>Successor entities in the event of a corporate restructuring or merger</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="s6">6. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>We retain personal data for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes outlined in this policy and to comply with applicable law. Specifically:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Account and KYC records: 7 years after account closure (CBSL requirement)</li>
        <li>Transaction records: 10 years (SEC requirement)</li>
        <li>Correspondence and call recordings: 5 years</li>
        <li>Marketing consent records: 3 years after last interaction</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="s7">7. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>Subject to applicable Sri Lankan law, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Access a copy of the personal data we hold about you</li>
        <li>Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete data</li>
        <li>Request erasure of data where retention is no longer justified</li>
        <li>Object to processing based on our legitimate interests</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent to marketing at any time</li>
        <li>Lodge a complaint with the relevant regulatory authority</li>
      </ul>
      <p>To exercise these rights, please contact our Data Protection Officer at <a href="mailto:dpo@hnbib.lk">dpo@hnbib.lk</a>.</p>

      <h2 id="s8">8. Security</h2>
      <p>We implement appropriate technical and organisational measures to protect your personal data against unauthorised access, accidental loss, destruction, or disclosure. These include encryption, access controls, regular security audits, and staff training. However, no internet transmission is completely secure and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

      <h2 id="s9">9. Cookies</h2>
      <p>Our website uses cookies and similar technologies to enhance your experience. We use:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Essential cookies:</strong> required for site functionality (session management, security)</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics cookies:</strong> to understand how visitors use our site (anonymised data)</li>
        <li><strong>Preference cookies:</strong> to remember your display and language settings</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You can control cookies through your browser settings. Disabling essential cookies may impair site functionality.</p>

      <h2 id="s10">10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Material changes will be communicated via email to account holders or by a prominent notice on our website. The "Last updated" date at the top of this page reflects the most recent revision. Continued use of our services after changes constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.</p>

      <h2 id="s11">11. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>For privacy-related enquiries or to exercise your rights, please contact:</p>
      <p><strong>Data Protection Officer</strong><br>
      HNB Investment Bank Limited<br>
      No. 53 Dharmapala Mawatha, Colombo 03, Sri Lanka<br>
      Email: <a href="mailto:dpo@hnbib.lk">dpo@hnbib.lk</a><br>
      Tel: <a href="tel:+94112206206">+94 112 206 206</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
.legal-body { max-width:760px; margin:0 auto; }
.legal-body h2 { font-size:1.3rem; margin:2.5rem 0 .75rem; color:var(--primary); }
.legal-body h3 { font-size:1rem; font-weight:700; margin:1.5rem 0 .5rem; }
.legal-body p, .legal-body li { font-size:.95rem; line-height:1.8; color:var(--ink); opacity:.85; }
.legal-body ul { padding-left:1.5rem; }
.legal-body li { margin-bottom:.4rem; }
.legal-meta { font-size:.8rem; opacity:.5; margin-bottom:2.5rem; }
.legal-toc { background:oklch(0.94 0.015 244); border-radius:var(--radius); padding:1.5rem 2rem; margin-bottom:3rem; }
.legal-toc h4 { font-size:.85rem; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:.08em; margin:0 0 .75rem; opacity:.6; }
.legal-toc ol { margin:0; padding-left:1.2rem; }
.legal-toc li { font-size:.9rem; margin-bottom:.35rem; }
.legal-toc a { color:var(--primary); text-decoration:none; }
.legal-toc a:hover { text-decoration:underline; }
</style>
